titleStmt.title: The Lords Ambassadours of the States Gernerall of the Netherlands their propositions unto the honourable Houses of Parliament; as they were in French presented unto the right honourable the Lord Grey of Warke, &c. Speaker of the Lords House, and the right worshipfull William Lenthall esquire, Speaker of the House of Commons the fourteenth of this instant March, 1643.

notesStmt.note: At end of text: Delivered by the Lords Amassadours of the Lords the Sates Generall, to the Speakers of both Houses of Parliament at Westminster this 14 of March, 1643.
Reproduction of the original in the Guildhall Library, London.
